OPTION 2: Commercial License
=============================

If you wish to use DeMoD in a commercial product (software plugins or
physical hardware) without the GPLv3 source disclosure requirements:

Purchase a Commercial License for $249 (one-time, perpetual per developer):
  - Unlimited commercial plugins (100% of software revenue is yours)
  - Unlimited physical hardware devices with modest revenue share:
    * 3% of hardware device sales revenue to DeMoD
    * 100% of software plugin revenue to you
  - No splash screens, telemetry, or monthly fees
  - Perpetual use (even if you cease subscription/updates)

Downloads & Purchase: https://demod.dev/license

When you distribute DeMoD under the Commercial License, you may:
  - Keep source code proprietary
  - Distribute compiled binaries without source disclosure
  - Distribute plugins and hardware without GPL compliance requirements
  - If selling hardware, report sales via the DeMoD revenue tracking system

SPECIAL TERMS: FAUST DSP SOURCES
================================

All .dsp source files in dsp/effects/ and dsp/lib/demod_skill.lib are subject
to separate copyright and licensing terms:

  - Your authored .dsp files retain YOUR original copyright
  - Faust itself is licensed under GPLv2+ (see FAUST-LICENSE if included)
  - The compiled output (.so libraries, plugin binaries) from your .dsp sources
    is governed by whichever DeMoD license you have (GPLv3 or Commercial)
  - You may use any compatible license for your original .dsp source code

Example:
  - You author "mycustom_reverb.dsp" -> YOUR copyright on the source
  - You compile to "mycustom_reverb.so" -> Governed by DeMoD's license (GPLv3 or Commercial)
  - If you choose Commercial License, your .dsp source remains proprietary
  - If you choose GPLv3, your .dsp source and compiled .so must comply with GPLv3

DEPENDENCY LICENSES
===================

DeMoD includes or depends on the following open-source components:

Included in repository (plugin/vendor/):
  - CPLUG (Unlicense - public domain)
  - PUGL (ISC License)
  - CLAP C API (MIT License)
  - VST3 C API (Dual: GPLv3 / Proprietary Steinberg License)

External dependencies (installed separately):
  - JACK2 (GPLv2+)
  - Faust (GPLv2+)
  - GHC / Haskell libraries (various open-source licenses)
  - Cairo (LGPL)
  - Lua 5.4 (MIT)

When you distribute DeMoD under the Commercial License, you must verify
compliance with these dependency licenses. Most are permissive; some (VST3)
may require separate licensing from Steinberg for commercial plugin distribution.

HARDWARE LICENSING: CRYPTOGRAPHIC VERIFICATION
================================================

If shipping physical hardware (guitar pedals, interfaces, effects, etc.) under
the Commercial License, DeMoD uses a simple, privacy-friendly SHA256-based
verification system to track revenue share -- no per-device activation, no
telemetry, no runtime checks.

How it works:
  1. You receive a secret 256-bit hardware license key with your Commercial License
  2. You embed this key in your build process (Zig snippet provided)
  3. The build outputs a SHA256 hash of (firmware + key)
  4. You ship hardware with this hash (in metadata or firmware version screen)
  5. Each quarter, you report: product name, hash, units sold, revenue
  6. DeMoD verifies the hash matches your licensed key; calculates 3% share

Your privacy:
  - DeMoD never sees your actual firmware binary
  - Your license key stays on your machine only
  - No telemetry in shipped firmware
  - Batch reporting only (no per-device tracking)
  - GDPR/CCPA compliant

Implementation:
  - Read full specification: HARDWARE_LICENSING.md in this repository
  - Build helper (Zig): scripts/demod_hw_license.zig (copy into your build.zig)
  - Verification tool (Python): scripts/verify_hardware_revenue.py (reference implementation)

Example revenue calculation:
  - You ship 87 guitar pedal units
  - Total revenue from sales: $105,000
  - DeMoD 3% share: $3,150
  - You receive invoice; pay via Stripe/ACH
  - Detailed audit trail available in your DeMoD account

Non-compliance:
  - If you report false revenue, or use an unverified firmware hash,
    the full reported revenue is owed to DeMoD (not just 3%)
  - Disputes are resolved via audit (we request firmware binary for verification)
  - See HARDWARE_LICENSING.md for dispute resolution process

GPLv3 hardware:
  - If you distribute under GPLv3, no revenue share applies
  - Hardware source must be published under GPLv3
  - No secret key required

CHOOSING YOUR LICENSE
